00:29:39.860 --> 00:29:41.970
to Panther Server.

00:29:42.770 --> 00:29:46.280
And that's something that's been really
dear to my heart because I deal with a

00:29:46.310 --> 00:29:49.810
lot of large accounts and they're like,
man, those cows are just killing us,

00:29:50.120 --> 00:29:50.300
right?

00:29:50.320 --> 00:29:54.930
The price, the pricing,
and I met this customer about,

00:29:54.930 --> 00:30:00.760
what is it, about 16 months ago,
and he has 1,000 Windows NT servers

00:30:00.760 --> 00:30:03.050
and Windows 2000 servers.

00:30:03.060 --> 00:30:05.410
And they're like...

00:30:06.340 --> 00:30:09.840
We would really like to migrate
those servers over to the Mac.

00:30:09.900 --> 00:30:13.980
I mean, he's the CIO of the company,
